You&#39;re using JUnit 5, so you shouldn&#39;t mix JUnit 4 into it just to get `assertThat`. That&#39;s part of a separate dependency, Hamcrest. JUnit 4 has a dependency on Hamcrest, but for JUnit 5 that integration has been removed. Instead, just include Hamcrest yourself (instead of JUnit 4):

```
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.hamcrest&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;hamcrest&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;2.2&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

