The model, in this case `DefaultMutableTreeNode`, doesn&#39;t do its own rendering. It&#39;s just for storing data.

All rendering is done through implementations of [TreeCellRenderer][1]. There is one provided implementation, [DefaultTreeCellRenderer][2].

The best way to go forward is to create a sub class of `DefaultTreeCellRenderer`, and override its `getTreeCellRendererComponent` method. For example:
```
public Component getTreeCellRendererComponent(JTree tree,
        Object value,
        boolean sel,
        boolean expanded,
        boolean leaf,
        int row,
        boolean hasFocus) {

    Component component = super.getTreeCellRendererComponent(tree, value, sel, expanded, leaf, row, hasFocus);
    if (value == searched) {
        component.setBackground(Color.RED);
    }
    return component;
}
```

  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/19/docs/api/java.desktop/javax/swing/tree/TreeCellRenderer.html
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/19/docs/api/java.desktop/javax/swing/tree/DefaultTreeCellRenderer.html

